<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="82" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1722,2034]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1758,1783]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[333,560,1758,1783]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Plateros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandescapularis">
<emphasis box="[333,560,1758,1783]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">P. grandescapularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirsch, 1865" authorityName="Kirsch" authorityYear="1865" box="[721,1033,1758,1783]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Plateros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bogotensis">
<emphasis box="[721,873,1758,1783]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">P. bogotensis</emphasis>
Kirsch, 
<number box="[977,1033,1758,1782]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" value="1865.0">1865</number>
</taxonomicName>
mainly by the shape and color of pronotum, first antennomeres ratio and by the leg coloration.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="83" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1722,2034]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,365,1830,1855]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">Redescription</emphasis>
: Body with ventral surface dark brown. Head dark brown, eyes small, interocular distance 
<number box="[1387,1421,1830,1854]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" value="1.7">1.7</number>
x longer than eye diameter. Antennae subserrate, antennomere 
<number box="[875,889,1866,1890]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" value="4.0">4</number>
as long as 5, 
<date box="[1071,1099,1866,1890]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">2x</date>
longer than antennomere 
<number box="[1415,1431,1866,1890]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" value="3.0">3</number>
. Mandibles well developed, slender, labial palpi short, maxillary palpi elongate, palpomere 
<number box="[1165,1179,1902,1926]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" value="4.0">4</number>
wide, 
<number box="[1254,1289,1902,1926]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" value="1.2">1.2</number>
x longer than palpomere 
<number box="[276,290,1938,1962]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" value="2.0">2</number>
and 
<date box="[343,371,1938,1962]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">
<number box="[343,357,1938,1962]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" value="2.0">2</number>
x
</date>
longer than palpomere 
<number box="[635,651,1938,1962]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" value="3.0">3</number>
. Pronotum subpentagonal, 
<number box="[954,988,1938,1962]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" value="1.1">1.1</number>
x wider than long medially, longitudinal median line channeled at basal ½, posterior angles obliquely projected backwards, posterior margin slightly bisinuate. Pronotum dark brown with lateral margins yellow. Scutellum dark brown with emargination distally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,580]" pageId="6" pageNumber="83">
Elytra dark brown with yellow portions from humeral region to distal 
<number box="[949,957,151,165]" pageId="6" pageNumber="83" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number box="[964,972,170,184]" pageId="6" pageNumber="83" value="5.0">5</number>
, forming a transversal band at this point, each elytron with 
<number box="[354,368,193,217]" pageId="6" pageNumber="83" value="9.0">9</number>
costae, primary costae stronger, regular reticulate cells subsquare, pubescent, 
<number box="[1252,1287,193,217]" pageId="6" pageNumber="83" value="3.2">3.2</number>
x longer than humeral width. Prosternum trapezoidal, legs compressed, dark brown, femur slightly compressed, as long as tibia, 
<date box="[151,179,265,289]" pageId="6" pageNumber="83">
<number box="[151,164,265,289]" pageId="6" pageNumber="83" value="3.0">3</number>
x
</date>
longer than trochanter. Female abdominal sternum 
<number box="[770,784,265,289]" pageId="6" pageNumber="83" value="9.0">9</number>
rounded distally. Female genitalia with coxites elongate, each one with oblique emargination medially. Valvifers integrated into coxites, as long as half of coxites. Styli ½ of coxites length, proctiger oval (
<figureCitation box="[493,574,340,364]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1787,1810]" captionTargetBox="[232,1353,163,1771]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[206,1381,141,1772]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 12. (1 – 5) Male genitalia. (1) Plateros brasiliensis (modified from Bocakova, 2001); (2) P. inhumeralis; (3) P. plaumanni; (4) P. bogotensis; (5) P. cristifer. (6 – 12) Female genitalia. (6) P. brasiliensis; (7) P. curtebilineatus; (8) P. w a g n e r i; (9) P. inhumeralis; (10) P. grandjeani; (11) P. grandescapularis; (12) P. duomaculatus. Scales: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/212349/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="83">
Fig. 
<number box="[545,574,340,364]" pageId="6" pageNumber="83" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
). Body length: 
<quantity box="[747,814,340,364]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="83" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
, humeral width: 
<quantity box="[1003,1093,340,364]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="83" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
